    what: 'All signal and price alerts were email-only (plus a nominally-implemented but non-functional Slack/Discord webhook path — User.notification_webhook does not actually exist as a DB field; the call site uses getattr(..., None) which always evaluates to None, so that delivery path has silently never fired). No browser push notifications, no mobile push. Traders miss signals while away from email.',
    fix: 'Implemented the deferred Web Push half: PushSubscription DB model (auto-created via the existing create_all mechanism, no Alembic migration needed in this repo); VAPID key settings in common/config.py (empty by default — push fails open/no-ops if unconfigured, matching how email_provider="" already disables email rather than crashing); push_service.py using pywebpush, with automatic pruning of dead subscriptions (404/410 responses mean the browser revoked it); new /push/subscribe, /push/unsubscribe, /push/status, /push/vapid-public-key endpoints, registered in main.py and added to api-gateway\'s routing table (services/api-gateway/src/api/proxy.py). Wired into BOTH existing alert-firing code paths in scheduler.py — signal alerts and price alerts — right alongside the existing email send.\n\nFrontend: a minimal service worker (public/sw.js) handling push display + notification-click focus/navigate; lib/push.ts wrapping subscribe/unsubscribe + VAPID key base64 encoding; a new "Push Notifications" toggle in the Notifications section of settings.tsx, with browser-support detection and a clear error message if push isn\'t configured server-side or permission is denied.\n\nDeployed to production: generated a real VAPID keypair (added to the EC2 .env, never committed), rebuilt the market-data image (pywebpush installed, push_subscriptions table auto-created and verified via a real schema query), rebuilt api-gateway (routing table fix) and frontend (service worker + settings UI) images, all recreated with --no-deps to avoid the documented mass-container-sweep pitfall (confirmed via before/after docker ps diffs that only the intended container was touched each time). Verified end-to-end through the real gateway path with a real user token: GET /push/vapid-public-key returns the real configured key, GET /push/status correctly reports push_available=true and subscription_count=0 (no browser has subscribed yet).',
    implementedNote: 'Done 2026-07-10. Slack/Discord webhook delivery (T230-ALERTING-SLACK-DISCORD) was previously marked done in this tracker but is actually dead code today — the User.notification_webhook field it depends on does not exist on the current model, so that call site always no-ops via its own getattr(..., None) fallback. Not fixed as part of this pass (out of scope — this pass was specifically the Web Push half); noting it here since it surfaced while wiring push into the same alert-firing code paths. Push notifications are the real, working third channel as of this deploy.',
