    fix: 'Added compound_conditions JSON column to PriceAlert (shared/db/models.py — a new column on an existing, already-populated table, so it required the same manual ALTER TABLE pattern as the notification_webhook incident earlier this session; ran it proactively this time before deploy, not reactively after a crash). Up to 3 AND-conditions per alert across volume_ratio (RVOL, via the T241-audit-fixed /stocks/{symbol}/rvol endpoint), rsi (read from the stored DB signal\'s reasons.rsi, same live=false source of truth check_signal_alerts() uses), and signal (BUY/SELL/HOLD/WAIT equality). New _evaluate_compound_conditions() in scheduler.py runs after the base price condition passes and before an alert fires — ANY unavailable or failing metric fails the whole alert closed (no partial fires), since compound alerts are opt-in noise reduction. Per-run caches (signal_cache/rvol_cache) avoid re-fetching the same symbol\'s data across multiple compound alerts. A matched compound-condition summary is appended to the alert\'s note before it\'s sent, so the delivered email/webhook shows exactly which extra conditions fired, not just the base price trigger. Frontend: alerts.tsx create form gained an "Also require (AND)" builder (add up to 3 rows, each a metric+operator+value picker), and the alert list shows a green "AND ..." badge summarizing any compound conditions on an existing alert.',
