    what: '(1) _scan_for_entries had no per-symbol cooldown after stop_hit exits. After a stop triggered, the next scan (running continuously) would immediately re-enter the same stock at the new lower price if the signal was still BUY. (2) Decision engine routes.py received signal.ts as a naive datetime string from the HTTP request (no Z suffix). fromisoformat returned a naive datetime; subtracting from datetime.now(timezone.utc) raised "can\'t subtract offset-naive and offset-aware datetimes" → fallback to _should_enter(). (3) signal_for() persist path called generate_all_signals() and stored the result directly without applying event-intelligence catalyst adjustments.',
    fix: '(1) Added per-symbol post-stop cooldown query in _scan_for_entries before the candidate loop: builds _recently_stopped set of symbols that hit a stop within stop_cooldown_hours (default 24h). Added skip check in the candidate loop. (2) decision-engine routes.py: after fromisoformat, added tzinfo=None guard — if parsed datetime is naive, replace with UTC. (3) signal_for() persist path now calls event-intelligence /catalyst/{symbol} (same 2s timeout, fail-silent) and applies the same _cat_adj logic as _bulk_persist before writing to DB.',
    implementedNote: 'Fixed 2026-06-25. Deployed: paper_trading_engine.py + decision-engine routes.py + signal-engine routes.py. Frontend rebuild for improvements.tsx.',
