    impact: 'Low — Fear & Greed momentum component (_score_at) returns 0.0 instead of the actual 20-day SPX return when the price series has exactly 21 bars. Edge case on short series but produces a subtly lower momentum score, slightly biasing Fear & Greed toward neutral.',
    title: 'T163-A: fear_greed momentum guard uses strict < instead of <= — off-by-one misses len=21 boundary',
    what: '`abs(i-20) < len(spx_close)` — when i=-1, abs(-21)=21. Requires len>21 (>=22) before computing iloc[-21]. But iloc[-21] is valid when len>=21. The len=21 case falls back to r=0.0.',
    fix: 'Changed to `abs(i-20) <= len(spx_close)`. iloc[-21] is valid when len>=21. The condition `21 <= 21` is True, so the boundary case is now handled correctly. First attempt used `<= len-1` (equivalent to `< len`, same bug) — corrected to `<= len`.',
    implementedNote: 'Done 2026-06-24 — routes.py line 383: `< len(spx_close)` → `<= len(spx_close)`.',
