    fix: 'Fixed 2026-07-05 (applies to all NEW scale-ins going forward — 2 existing open positions intentionally left uncorrected, see below) — implemented exactly the approach the tracker\'s own fix note recommended: on scale-in, entry_price is now blended as a weighted average of the original and added lots (new_entry = (old_shares*old_entry + added_shares*add_price) / (old_shares+added_shares), using the same slippage-adjusted fill price the cash deduction already uses), and entry_shares is incremented by the same added_shares amount — mirroring how T232-PT6 already correctly handles the scale-OUT side (which intentionally does NOT touch entry_price, since a partial sale of the same lot has no new cost basis to blend). Confirmed no other code path breaks from a mid-trade entry_price change: the local `entry` variable in _monitor_positions is re-read fresh from trade.entry_price every cycle, so downstream breakeven-stop-move and scale-out pnl_pct calculations correctly pick up the blended value on their next run — and use it correctly, since a position\'s true breakeven point is the blended cost basis, not the original tranche\'s price. trade.stop_loss (the fixed floor used by all trailing-stop calculations) is a separate field, untouched by this change. Compile-checked (3.11 + 3.12, matches market-data\'s 3.12.13 container). Verified the arithmetic with a standalone reproduction: for a 10-share $100 entry scaled in with 2.5 shares at $110, the old buggy calc overstated close-time P&L by $25 (11%) on a $120 exit; the fixed blended-entry calc ($102.00 blended entry) exactly matches the true sum of each lot\'s independent P&L ($225.00). Could not exercise the live code path end-to-end (zero open paper trades in the local dev DB at deploy time) — verified via compile-check, live container restart with clean logs, and the independently-confirmed arithmetic instead. CORRECTION to an earlier draft of this note: initially checked only the local dev DB for existing SCALE_IN trades (found none) and wrongly concluded there was nothing to correct — on checking PRODUCTION\'s DB found 2 open positions (UPST id=23, opened 2026-06-18; IMVT id=7, opened 2026-06-17) that genuinely scaled in under the pre-fix code and carry a stale, understated entry_price (both also had subsequent scale-outs, making exact historical reconstruction from notes-text nontrivial). Flagged this to the user per the tracker\'s own guidance (same category of decision as T232-PT6\'s UPST/IMVT correction) rather than silently leaving it undocumented or guessing at a correction — user chose to leave both positions as-is rather than risk introducing a new error via manual reconstruction, accepting the modest known bias on these 2 legacy positions in exchange for not touching live financial data by hand. Revisit if/when either position is closer to closing.',
