    impact: 'Medium — found while writing docs/SELF_IMPROVEMENT_LOOP.md, which required re-reading every calibration endpoint\'s exact logic rather than trusting prior descriptions. calibrate_ml_weight (routes.py:1051-1197) computes a chronological 70/30 split (line 1137-1141) and displays a validation-set accuracy curve, which led T232-OC3\'s own tracker entry to describe it as "already doing a 70/30 temporal split correctly" — the model other endpoints should copy. On closer reading, the split exists but doesn\'t actually gate anything: the weight selection loop (line 1150-1159) picks optimal_weight by maximizing accuracy on calib_obs (the TRAINING slice), and only computes validation-set accuracy afterward (line 1176-1183) for the response payload — set_ml_weight_global_cap(optimal_weight) at line 1185 runs unconditionally regardless of what the validation slice shows. This means the weight actually written to ml_weight_override.json (and used by every subsequent signal fusion calc) can be an in-sample-optimal choice that never independently proved itself on unseen data — the same failure class T232-OC3/T234-SIG-INSAMPLE-GATE-TUNING already fixed elsewhere, present here in the ONE function those fixes cited as the correct reference pattern.',
